description:
In this episode, we discover the historic invention of the printing press. It was created in the 15th century by German Goldsmith, Johannes Gutenberg, and revolutionised society and the world of literature by fundamentally changing the way that people communicated. The Gutenberg Press changed communication, making the quick spread of new ideas possible. It had a huge impact on the Reformation in the 16th century as it meant copies of the Bible and other tracts could spread far and wide.

To find out more information about the Gutenberg Press visit our website to read our extended article.
